## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Scope

Feature parity synchronization across 3 MCP Code Intelligence implementations (Python, Node.js, Kotlin). Ports missing features to achieve 100% feature parity.

**Key gaps:** - Python & Kotlin lack: Core Memory, Conversation History, Structured Map (from Node.js) - Node.js lacks: Cache layer, File Watcher, Viewer UI (from Python/Kotlin) - Kotlin lacks: Nested Detection

### 1.2 Out of Scope

* Creating new features not present in any implementation
* Changing the MCP protocol specification
* Unifying the 3 implementations into a single codebase

### 1.3 Preliminary Requirement

* All 3 MCP implementations must be stable
* Node.js must have Core Memory, Conversation, Structured Map functional
* Python must have Cache layer and Viewer UI functional
* KSA-139 should be completed or in progress

## 2. Business Requirements

### 2.2 User Stories

| # | Story | Priority |
| --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Core Memory (Pinned Entries + Auto-Recall) — Port to Python & Kotlin | MUST HAVE |
| 2 | Conversation History — Port to Python & Kotlin | MUST HAVE |
| 3 | Structured Map & Entity Index — Port to Python & Kotlin | MUST HAVE |
| 4 | Cache Layer for Orchestration — Port to Node.js | MUST HAVE |
| 5 | File Watcher — Port to Node.js | SHOULD HAVE |
| 6 | Viewer UI — Port to Node.js & Kotlin | COULD HAVE |
| 7 | Nested Detection — Port to Kotlin | SHOULD HAVE |

### Story Details

**STORY 1: Core Memory** — mem\_pin tool (pin, unpin, list, reorder, get\_context, budget). Schema migration, CoreMemoryManager, 2000-token budget, auto-recall hook.

**STORY 2: Conversation History** — mem\_conversation tool (save\_turn, get\_session, list\_sessions, search, summarize). Schema migration, ConversationRepository, session grouping.

**STORY 3: Structured Map** — mem\_map tool (get, update, search\_entity, search\_topic, reextract). Schema migration, StructuredMapExtractor, EntityRepository.

**STORY 4: Cache Layer** — orchestration/cache/ module. LRU + TTL, cache registry/kb\_search/code\_intel, invalidation on changes.

**STORY 5: File Watcher** — chokidar/fs.watch, debounce 500ms, configurable globs, graceful error handling.

**STORY 6: Viewer UI** — Port Python static HTML/JS, configurable port, WebSocket/SSE updates.

**STORY 7: Nested Detection** — Detect child MCP servers with find\_tools, register tools, handle lifecycle.

## 3. Dependencies

| Dependency | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| KSA-139 | System | Cache layer related |
| Node.js implementations | System | Reference for F1/F2/F3 |
| Python implementations | System | Reference for Cache/Viewer |
| chokidar | External | File watching |
| SQLite | External | Schema migrations |

## 5. Risks

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Schema migration breaks data | High | Reversible migrations with backup |
| Ported features differ from reference | Medium | Integration tests comparing outputs |
| File watcher high CPU | Medium | Configurable patterns, debouncing |
| Large scope delays delivery | Medium | Prioritize HIGH items first |

## 6. Non-Functional Requirements

| Category | Requirement | Target |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Performance | Core Memory auto-recall | < 5ms |
| Performance | Conversation search | < 50ms |
| Performance | Cache hit | < 1ms |
| Performance | File watcher re-index | < 2s |
| Compatibility | Cross-platform | Win/Mac/Linux |
| Security | Viewer UI | Localhost-only |

